  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "While individual feeding systems are already in use for swine farming (65), similar advancements are less prevalent in dairy cattle and virtually non-existent in poultry farming due to the challenges of individual care.",
    "We propose adapting these advanced feeders to other species, addressing their specific nutritional and behavioral needs, and overcoming the limitations of current group-based feeding systems (66).",
    "Incorporating AI algorithms to analyze feeding data can help predict health issues before they become clinically apparent (67, 68).",
    "This proactive approach aligns with precision farming's goal of individualized care.",
    "Growing research attention suggests that cognition of these species is more complex than originally thought (69, 70) and reducing stress as well as providing for these animals' biological and social needs can have positive effects for both welfare and economics (71)."
  ],
